Light and Location - An Intoxicating Mix

Comprises open plan living, kitchen, main bedroom with ensuite, and desirable north facing balcony. Enjoy an enviable lifestyle with public transport, Smith and Gertrude Streets right at your doorstep.

Description:
Superb City-Living in the Unique 'Oxley' Apartments
Designed by award winning architects Elenberg Fraser, the Oxley Apartment Complex is perfectly positioned in the heart of Collingwood's Foy heritage precinct. This stunning single bedroom is both modern & unique, offering a streamlined contemporary layout maximising natural light throughout.
The open-plan living & dining area featuring floor to ceiling windows opens unto an ultra-spacious & versatile wintergarden-style balcony, offering extra efficiency in being a wind, noise and weather proof outdoor space throughout all the seasons. A convenient kitchen with stone benches, stainless steel appliances and glass splashback. Comprising a generous and well-lit bedroom featuring large built in wardrobe and ample natural light, as well as an immaculately presented and ultra-spacious bathroom with floor to ceiling tiles and high-end fittings. Other features include double-glazed windows, block out roller blinds, split-system with heating and cooling unit, rooftop garden terrace, outdoor BBQ area & plunge-pool. The Uniquely designed & lush exterior landscapes provides occupants with a secure sanctuary to call home.
Conveniently located in close proximity to Smith Streets bars & cafes, renowned restaurants, cosmopolitan shopping precincts, The East-Melbourne hospital precinct, Collingwood train station & trams, Fitzroy Gardens & the CBD. This apartment is a perfect opportunity for astute investors or first home buyers.

Description:
HERITAGE WARMTH MEETS CRISP CONTEMPORARY STYLE: AN URBAN OASIS
Renovated with exceptional flair, this wider than usual Victorian terrace is one of the inner-north's most appealing offerings, set in a quiet street bordering Collingwood's vibrant design and business enclave, close to cafes, the Convent Arts precinct and all public transport options. Traditional Collingwood design elements - soaring ceilings, mellow brick and timber detail - combine with large areas of glazing to create a light-filled ambience, with green views to a tranquil garden and internal light court. A cleverly expanded floor plan comprises two airy double bedrooms (one with built-in wardrobes) opening from a decorative arched hallway; an expansive living/dining room open to a showpiece kitchen with European appliances; stunning bathroom with overbath rain-shower; a versatile study/storeroom, plus laundry and second WC. With scope to refocus the outdoor space as an entertainer's zone using prepared landscape architect's plans, this captivating residence features double glazing, gas heating, split system air conditioning and continuous flow gas HWS. Prepare to be delighted! Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
A Vibrant City Fringe Lifestyle
This stunning apartment is situated in arguably Collingwoods most stylish apartment complex. With a generous floor-plan allowing for relaxed living and providing a very desirable base to enjoy an inner urban lifestyle moments from Smith Street in the heart of Collingwood. The interior features a spacious living area with a sleek stone and stainless steel kitchen opening to a large balcony, master bedroom with ensuite, large second bedroom with separate bathroom and European laundry.
Cutting Edge Architect-designed Complex
Vibrant City Fringe Lifestyle
Secure intercom entry
R/C air conditioning
Large balcony ideal for entertaining
Open plan living
Basement car park (1)
Storage cage
Amenities
Amenities include the trendy Project 49 café in the building plus basement car parking and a storage cage.
Location
Enjoy a walk-to lifestyle moments from the myriad of bars, coffee shops and restaurants in the Smith Street precinct in the vibrant heart of Collingwood; just short stroll to the Fitzroy and Treasury Gardens or the CBD. Alternatively it is minutes from Australias best sporting precinct including the MCG, the Tennis Centre and AAMI Park. Other attractions include easy access to public transport options and other popular lifestyle suburbs such as Richmond or South Yarra.

Description:
Luxury in the sky - beautiful space & breathtaking views
A luxury domain on the East Melbourne fringe, this stunning new apartment is pure designer indulgence with breathtaking views sweeping from the city skyline to the northern ranges. Spanning the entire sculptural west-face of John Wardle Architects' exclusive new Holme complex, this compelling 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom apartment is substantial, chic and absolutely spectacular. Banks of full-height, double glazed windows capture views at every turn as the sophisticated space unfolds revealing high-end features, deluxe style and an entertainment terrace for world-class alfresco dining. Below is a vibrant cultural cornucopia with art galleries, cafes, restaurants and specialty shops including Gertrude Street while just nearby is the Fitzroy Gardens, hospitals precinct and the CBD. This outstanding new 11th-floor oasis boasts 3 brilliant bedrooms (BIRs; main with a Mt Macedon vista and beautiful ensuite), sensational open-plan living and dining area, entertainers' kitchen showcasing ASKO appliances and Vintec wine fridge, stylish main bathroom, laundry, ducted heating/cooling, video intercom security, excellent storage, bespoke joinery, oak floors, 2 basement car spaces and storage cage. The building includes a communal area with kitchen, fireside lounge, teppanyaki grill and garden.

Designed by award winning architects Elenberg Fraser, the Oxley Apartment Complex is perfectly positioned in the heart of Collingwood's Foy Heritage precinct. This stunning 2 bedroom is both modern & unique, offering a streamlined contemporary layout maximising natural light throughout.
The open-plan living & dining area featuring floor to ceiling windows opens unto an ultra-spacious balcony with outstretched sweeping views.
